# Getting the XR-3000 working and bookmarkable

## Why it hasn't been working

You've been opening the deck by **double-clicking the file**. When you do that, your
browser's address bar says `file:///...`

In that mode:

- **YouTube refuses to play.** That's the "Error 153" you saw. Google blocks video
  embedding from local files, deliberately. Nothing you do in the deck can fix it.
- **Nothing saves.** The browser blocks storage on local files, so your Tape Library
  is wiped every time.

This is not something you were doing wrong. It's a wall the browser puts up, and the
only way past it is to open the deck over `http://` or `https://` instead.

Once you've done the steps below, **both problems disappear permanently.**

---

## Putting it on GitHub Pages (free, permanent, bookmarkable)

You'll end up with a real web address like:

    https://yourname.github.io/xr3000/

You bookmark that, and from then on you just click the bookmark. It works on your
phone too.

### Step 1 — Make a GitHub account

Go to **github.com** and sign up, if you haven't already. It's free.

### Step 2 — Make a new repository

1. Click the **+** in the top-right, then **New repository**.
2. Name it: `xr3000`
3. Set it to **Public**. (Pages doesn't work on free private repos.)
4. Tick **Add a README file**.
5. Click **Create repository**.

### Step 3 — Upload the deck

1. On your new repo page, click **Add file** -> **Upload files**.
2. Drag in **`index.html`** (the file that came with this guide).

   The name matters. `index.html` is the name a web server looks for
   automatically, which is what gives you a clean URL.

3. Scroll down, click **Commit changes**.

### Step 4 — Turn on Pages

1. Click the **Settings** tab (top of the repo).
2. In the left sidebar, click **Pages**.
3. Under "Build and deployment":
   - **Source**: Deploy from a branch
   - **Branch**: `main`, folder `/ (root)`
4. Click **Save**.

### Step 5 — Wait a minute, then open it

Refresh the Settings -> Pages screen after a minute. It'll show:

    Your site is live at https://yourname.github.io/xr3000/

Click it. The deck loads. **Bookmark that page.**

---

## How you know it worked

- The red "opened from your hard drive" warning is **gone**.
- Paste a YouTube link, press LOAD, and it **actually plays**.
- Your Tape Library **survives a refresh**.

---

## Using it, once it's live

### Playing something

1. Paste a YouTube link into the loader box. A **playlist or album link works best**.
2. Press **LOAD**. The tape spins up and plays.

### Saving a tape to your library

The Tape Library at the bottom **is** your favourites. To put something in it:

1. Load and play a YouTube link (as above).
2. Press **RECORD** — it lights up red (armed).
3. Press **PLAY** — the tape rolls and starts logging tracks as they pass the heads.
4. Press **STOP** when you've had enough — it asks you to name the tape.
5. It appears as a card in **TAPE LIBRARY**. Click that card any time to load it back.

Recorded tapes are saved in your browser, tied to that web address. Because it's now
a proper URL, they'll still be there tomorrow.

### The BLANK C60 button

Ignore it for this. A blank is an empty cassette with nothing recorded on it — it's
only there so you can watch the mechanism run without loading any music. It plays no
part in saving your favourites.

---

## Keyboard shortcuts

| Key | Does |
|-----|------|
| Space | Play / Pause |
| Left / Right arrow | Rewind / Fast forward |
| Shift + Left / Right | Previous / Next track |
| Up / Down arrow | Output level |
| S | Stop |
| R | Record |
| E | Eject |
| P | Power |

